# ===== Secrets (NEVER commit) =====
# The Cloudflare DNS-01 token and any other app secret are written to APP_DATA_DIR at
# runtime (e.g. brooksbuwo-caddy/data/cf-api-token) and must never be committed. These
# rules are a hard backstop against `git add .` pulling a local secret into the repo.
cf-api-token
**/cf-api-token
**/data/cf-api-token
*.token
*.secret
.env
.env.*
*.env
!.env.example
!*.env.example
secrets/
**/secrets/
*.pem
*.key
*.p12
*.pfx
id_rsa
id_ed25519
*_rsa
*_ed25519
# Caddy runtime cert/account store (holds private keys) if it ever lands under a data dir
**/caddy-data/
**/caddy-config/
**/acme/

# ===== App runtime data (keep the dirs, ignore their contents) =====
# umbreld populates data/ subdirs at install; the repo ships them EMPTY via .gitkeep.
# Ignore everything written into data/ at runtime, but always keep the .gitkeep markers
# so the empty dirs still ship (this is what the secret-in-data/ pattern depends on).
**/data/**
!**/data/
!**/data/**/
!**/data/**/.gitkeep
!**/data/.gitkeep

# ===== OS / editor cruft =====
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*~
*.swp
*.swo
.idea/
.vscode/
*.sublime-*

# ===== Build / logs / temp =====
*.log
*.tmp
*.bak
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.pyc
